<h4 id="what-is-c-">What is C++ ?</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Direct map to hardware
    <ul>
      <li>of instructions and fundamental data types</li>
      <li>initially from c</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Zero-overhead abstraction
    <ul>
      <li>classes with constructors and destructors, inheritance, generic programming,
functional programming techniques</li>
      <li>initially from Simula</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Much of the inspiration came from operating system</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="the-future-of-c">The Future of C++</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Better at it for modern hardware and techniques.</li>
  <li>Compatibility/stability is a feature.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="key-strengths">Key Strengths:</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Software infrastructure</li>
  <li>resource-constrained applications</li>
</ol>

